OL,3,C'It will be the end of him': Wife's
OL,4,Cfears for husband if forced into care
OL,6,FMarian has been told he may have to go
OL,7,Finto a care home.
OL,9,F"I can't bear thinking about it," she
OL,10,Fsaid.
OL,12,F"I know it would be the end of him. It
OL,13,Fwould absolutely be the end of him. He
OL,14,Fhas 24-hour needs. That's me and
OL,15,Fcarers here at home with what he is
OL,16,Ffamiliar with and is happy."
OL,18,FJim now requires two carers a day to
OL,19,Fhelp with his complex needs.
