OL,3,C'It will be the end of him': Wife's
OL,4,Cfears for husband if forced into care
OL,6,F"Unfortunately, in common with all
OL,7,Fparts of the region, in some instances
OL,8,Fthe Western Trust finds it difficult
OL,9,Fto secure capacity to meet increasing
OL,10,Fdemand for domiciliary care,
OL,11,Fparticularly in more rural areas and
OL,12,Fwe acknowledge and apologise for the
OL,13,Fimpact of this on service users and
OL,14,Ftheir families.
OL,16,F"We know that there are increased
OL,17,Frisks for patients staying in hospital
OL,18,Fthat can lead to the patient
OL,19,Fdeteriorating.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/8
